name: Paul Goldschmidt
summary: The New York Yankees have reportedly agreed to a one-year, $12.5 million contract with former MVP Paul Goldschmidt to fill their first base vacancy. Goldschmidt, a six-time All-Star and four-time Silver Slugger, is expected to provide a significant boost to the Yankees' lineup. The move has also fueled speculation that the Yankees could make a trade for another All-Star infielder, Nolan Arenado of the St. Louis Cardinals, who has reportedly been seeking a trade. However, the Cardinals have rejected the Yankees' initial offer for Arenado.

summary: Ohio State football fans are urged to embrace joy amidst the team's intense performance. The #7 Tennessee Volunteers fell to the #6 Ohio State Buckeyes in the College Football Playoff, while Oklahoma State's coaching staff undergoes significant changes. In a historic first, Ohio State and Tennessee face off in Ohio Stadium for the CFP, with Ohio State preparing for a spectacular drone show and "Scarlet Glow" illumination.
